        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 25 at 2:27PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 227 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers over East
Greenbush, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
East Greenbush, Castleton-On-Hudson, West Sand Lake, Wyantskill,
Averill Park, Selkirk, Wynantskill, North Greenbush, Brunswick, Sand
Lake, Poestenkill, East Nassau, Brookview, Van Hoesen Station, Albia,
West Stephentown, Beckers Corners, Millers Corners, Taborton, and
Barberville.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 90 between exits 10 and 9.
Interstate 87 between exits 21A and 22.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring and may lead to localized
flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
